The documents that must be prepared and submitted before the bid‑submission deadline are the bid documents, which the Implementation Consultant (IC) is required to compile in accordance with ADB bid standards and guidance. These documents include:  
- a design‑criteria document that sets out the applicable standards and project‑specific information for bidders;  
- a description of the overall work to be performed under the contract;  
- the scope of works;  
- performance designs that build on the condition assessment;  
- sufficient drawings and schematics for bid preparation;  
- appropriate specifications related to the design‑criteria standards;  
- bidder‑qualification forms;  
- bid forms;  
- suggested required bonds and bid arrangements; and  
- suggested selection criteria for bid evaluation.  

All of these items must be assembled and submitted before the bid‑submission deadline, following the ADB procurement procedures and the guidance provided by the IC. [rfp.pdf, p:6]

